SilShape
public class ArrowLineShape
extends LineShape

A Arrowline that is drawn on the screen. In addition to the properties of a normal Silhouette Line shape, a arrow-line also has the following user settable-properties:

  1. X1, Y1: The first endpoint
  2. X2, Y2: The second endpoint
  3. arrowFilled: true means that the arrowheads should be filled. false means that they should be open *
  4. ArrowLength: The length of the arrowhead
  5. ArrowWidth: The width of the arrowhead

Description copied from class: LineShape
Draws a line shape to the screen. This method should never be called directly by an application. To get a line shape to appear on the screen, either add it to a Silhouette canvas or to a composite shape that has been added to a Silhouette canvas.
